  "prompt": "Is there an inpatient Drug and Alcohol Rehab Center in Shasta County California?",
  "response": "Yes, there are inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers in Shasta County, California. One notable facility is **Shasta County Health and Human Services Agency**, which offers substance abuse treatment services, including inpatient options. Another option is **Northern Valley Catholic Social Service (NVCSS)**, which provides comprehensive substance abuse treatment programs.\n\nAdditionally, **Hill Country Health & Wellness Center** in Round Mountain, which is part of Shasta County, offers addiction treatment services. It\u2019s advisable to contact these facilities directly for the most up-to-date information on their programs, availability, and admission requirements.\n\nYou can also use resources like the **Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA)** treatment locator (https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/) to find more options in the area.",
